{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-2hg","title":"v0.2 BEAD-7: Magnetometer driver","description":"firmware-overlay/src/modules/CompassModule/Magnetometer.{h,cpp} — QMC5883L driver on Wire1 (I2C 0x0D) per TDD section 10. begin() returning InitResult enum (OK/NOT_FOUND/INIT_FAILED); read() with DRDY polling; heading() applying calibration offsets; setCalibration/getCalibration. Init: chip ID 0xFF at reg 0x0D, write 0x01 to SETPERIOD, 0x1D to CTRL1, 0x40 to CTRL2. Acceptance: make build succeeds; on real hardware begin() returns OK with chip connected, NOT_FOUND with bus empty, INIT_FAILED with wrong chip ID; heading() smooth in [0,360); no blocking longer than DRDY_TIMEOUT_MS. Depends on BEAD-5.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T06:04:43Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T06:58:32Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T06:58:32Z","close_reason":"Magnetometer driver complete. firmware-overlay/src/modules/CompassModule/Magnetometer.{h,cpp} written. begin() returns InitResult enum (OK/NOT_FOUND/INIT_FAILED) based on Wire1 ACK + chip ID 0xFF check. Init writes SETPERIOD=0x01, CTRL1=0x1D (continuous, 200Hz, 8G, OSR512), CTRL2=0x40 (ROL_PTR). read() polls DRDY in STATUS reg with 10ms timeout, then burstReads 6 bytes (LE int16 X/Y/Z). heading() applies hard-iron offsets and atan2f. Uses Wire1 directly via Arduino API (BSP auto-creates Wire1 from PIN_WIRE1_*). Compiles in cross-build for arm-none-eabi-gcc. Hardware ACK + heading sweep verification deferred until QMC5883L hardware is wired.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-2hg","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-3up","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T01:05:28Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
