{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fvu","title":"BEAD-7: CompassUI — drawFrame, arrow rendering, input handling","description":"Create src/modules/CompassModule/CompassUI.h and CompassUI.cpp. Implements wantUIFrame(), interceptingKeyboardInput(), drawFrame(), handleInputEvent(). Arrow geometry: tip(0,-18), wings(±9,-4), tail(0,12) rotated by headingError using sinf/cosf (nRF52840 has FPU). Blinks at 500ms when signal lost \u003e90s. Screens: DISCOVERING node list, TRACKING compass, PAIR_INCOMING accept/reject, CALIBRATING sample counter, TRACKING_TREASURE with YOU'RE HERE at \u003c15m.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:37:10Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T04:03:44Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T04:03:44Z","close_reason":"CompassUI.h and CompassUI.cpp written for 240x135 ST7789 TFT; arrow at (72,67) with rotatePoint+fillTriangle, dim/blink modes, all 9 state sub-renderers, 800ms long-press input handling","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fvu","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-61d","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:39:00Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fvu","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-plu","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:39:00Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fvu","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-q18","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:59Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":3,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-61d","title":"BEAD-6: CompassModule — SinglePortModule + OSThread packet handler","description":"Create src/modules/CompassModule/CompassModule.h and CompassModule.cpp. Extends SinglePortModule (COMPASS_APP port) and OSThread. Implements handleReceived() dispatching all 8 CompassMsgType values, runOnce() scheduler driving TRACKED position updates and TRACKING timeout detection, and send helpers (sendCapabilityQuery, sendPairRequest, sendPairAccept, sendPairReject, sendSessionEnd). Static instance pointer.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:37:03Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:59:04Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:59:04Z","close_reason":"CompassModule.h and CompassModule.cpp written. SinglePortModule+OSThread, full packet dispatch for all 8 message types, sendCapabilityQuery/PairRequest/Accept/Reject/SessionEnd helpers, runOnce() driving calibration sample drain, pair timeout, tickTracked() position updates, tickTracking() session pause detection.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-61d","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-7si","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:56Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-61d","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fkf","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:57Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-61d","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-plu","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:58Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":3,"dependent_count":2,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-plu","title":"BEAD-5: CompassState — FSM and NVS persistence","description":"Create src/modules/CompassModule/CompassState.h and CompassState.cpp. Full state machine with states: IDLE, DISCOVERING, AWAITING_PAIR_ACCEPT, PAIR_INCOMING, TRACKING, TRACKED, TRACKING_TREASURE, SESSION_PAUSED, CALIBRATING. NVS namespace 'compass'. Treasure CRUD (max 5), calibration sample accumulation (min 50 samples), Desire-side update suppression (5min stationary keepalive).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:36:59Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:57:15Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:57:15Z","close_reason":"CompassState.h and CompassState.cpp written. Full 9-state FSM, FSCom-based persistence for cal/treasures/settings under /compass/, Desire-side suppression via CompassMath::distanceMeters.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-plu","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-q18","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:55Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":2,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fkf","title":"BEAD-3: Magnetometer driver — QMC5883L on Wire1","description":"Create src/modules/CompassModule/Magnetometer.h and Magnetometer.cpp. QMC5883L driver on Wire1 (I2C addr 0x0D). Implement begin() returning InitResult enum (OK/NOT_FOUND/INIT_FAILED), read() with DRDY polling, heading() applying calibration offsets, setCalibration()/getCalibration(). Init sequence: verify chip ID 0xFF at reg 0x0D, write 0x01 to SETPERIOD, 0x1D to CTRL1, 0x40 to CTRL2.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:36:54Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:57:13Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:57:13Z","close_reason":"Magnetometer.h and Magnetometer.cpp written. QMC5883L driver on Wire1: begin() probes 0x0D, verifies chip ID 0xFF, runs init sequence. DRDY-gated burst read. heading() applies hard-iron offsets.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-fkf","depends_on_id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-cdo","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-01T22:38:53Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-q18","title":"BEAD-4: CompassMath — bearing, distance, heading error","description":"Create src/modules/CompassModule/CompassMath.h and CompassMath.cpp. Pure stateless functions: bearing(fromLat,fromLon,toLat,toLon) using forward azimuth formula, distanceMeters() using Haversine, headingError(currentHeading,bearing) returning signed [-180,180] degrees. Inputs are integer lat/lon x1e7 matching GPS and protobuf convention.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:36:45Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:12Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:12Z","close_reason":"CompassMath.h and CompassMath.cpp written in src/modules/CompassModule/. bearing(), distanceMeters(), headingError() implemented using Haversine and forward azimuth formulas.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":2,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-7si","title":"BEAD-2: Protobuf definition — compass.proto + COMPASS_APP port","description":"Add compass.proto to protobufs/meshtastic/ defining CompassMsgType enum (8 values) and CompassPacket message. Add COMPASS_APP=300 to portnums.proto. Run bin/generate-proto.sh to produce nanopb generated files. Commit generated compass.pb.h and compass.pb.c.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:36:41Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:11Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:11Z","close_reason":"compass.proto written, COMPASS_APP=300 added to portnums.proto, nanopb codegen produced compass.pb.h/.pb.cpp and updated portnums.pb.h. All files in firmware dir.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-cdo","title":"BEAD-1: Variant patch — Wire1 instantiation","description":"variant.cpp for heltec_mesh_node_t114 does not instantiate Wire1 despite variant.h already defining WIRE_INTERFACES_COUNT=2 and PIN_WIRE1_SDA/SCL. Add TwoWire Wire1 instance to variant.cpp using NRF_TWIM1 peripheral. This is required for the QMC5883L magnetometer driver to function.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Nathan Barlow","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T03:36:35Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:09Z","closed_at":"2026-05-02T03:54:09Z","close_reason":"BSP auto-creates Wire1 from PIN_WIRE1_* defines in variant.h — confirmed by inspecting all other nRF52 variants with WIRE_INTERFACES_COUNT=2. No variant.cpp change needed.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-dyg","title":"Wire End-Session UI + fix long-press release in TRACKING (CUJ-7)","description":"Two related gaps: (1) no manual End-Session UI — sessions only end via 5min auto-pause or peer-initiated SESSION_END. Need a 'Compass: End Session' menu entry that calls CompassModule::sendSessionEnd(). (2) CompassUI::handleInputEvent in TRACKING/TRACKING_TREASURE/SESSION_PAUSED returns 1 on SELECT_LONG/BACK but doesn't actually do anything — the comment 'Release UI frame; tracking continues in background' is aspirational. Either implement a UI-minimized flag that makes wantUIFrame() return false while remaining in TRACKING, or wire the long-press to End Session. Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §9 and PRD CUJ-7.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:00Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:00Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-p82","title":"Wire Treasure UI: Save / Treasures-list / Navigate-to (CUJ-5, CUJ-6)","description":"CompassState has full Treasure CRUD (saveTreasure / treasure / deleteTreasure / startTreasureNav, max 5) but no UI surface invokes any of them. Add menu entries for: (1) Save current GPS as Treasure with label entry, (2) list saved Treasures, (3) select a Treasure to enter TRACKING_TREASURE state. CompassUI already has a drawTrackingTreasure renderer including the YOU'RE HERE \u003c15m banner. Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §9 and PRD CUJ-5/6.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:33:54Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:33:54Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-a86","title":"Wire calibration UI: menu entry → CALIBRATING state (CUJ-2)","description":"The firmware has a complete calibration FSM (CompassState::startCalibration / feedCalSample / finishCalibration / saveCalibrationFile) and CompassUI has a CALIBRATING-state renderer, but there's no menu entry to trigger startCalibration() from IDLE. As a result, all heading readings are uncalibrated raw QMC5883L output. Add a 'Compass: Calibrate' entry to the home banner menu (or a Compass sub-menu) that triggers CompassModule::instance-\u003estate()-\u003estartCalibration(). Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §9 and PRD CUJ-2.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:33:50Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:33:50Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-dp6","title":"Show \"Pair Rejected\" banner when REJECT received (UX polish)","description":"Currently when Bob rejects Alice's pair request, Alice's CompassState::onPairRejected() drops back to IDLE silently. Per PRD CUJ-3 error case: 'Alice's display shows Pair rejected by Bob. Returns to node list.' Add a brief banner / showSimpleBanner('Pair rejected') call before dropping back to IDLE. Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §6 Test 5 variant + PRD CUJ-3 error cases.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:09Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:09Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-h4a","title":"Wire Update-Interval setting UI (CUJ-4)","description":"CompassState has setUpdateIntervalSec() with persisted storage at /compass/settings, but no UI to invoke it. Stuck at 30s default. Per PRD §7, options are 10s/30s/60s/120s. Add a 'Compass: Settings: Update Interval' entry that lets the user pick from those four values. Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §9 and PRD §7.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:06Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:06Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"meshtastic-captains-compass-n35","title":"Wire Status UI: Compass diagnostics screen (CUJ-1)","description":"Magnetometer init result is currently logged to serial only ('Captain's Compass: mag init OK/NOT_FOUND/INIT_FAILED'). The PRD CUJ-1 calls for a Status screen showing the chip detection result + firmware version + calibration status. Add a 'Compass: Status' menu entry. The screen should report: mag chip detection result, calibration validity, last calibration sample count, firmware build SHA. Discovered during v0.2 manual QA. See docs/qa-issue-002-captains-compass.md §9 and PRD CUJ-1.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"nathanjbarlow@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:03Z","created_by":"Nathan Barlow","updated_at":"2026-05-02T07:34:03Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"memory","key":"v0-1-of-the-tdd-specified-upstream-firmware","value":"v0.1 of the TDD specified upstream firmware paths (src/modules/CompassModule/..., variants/...) without specifying how this repo physically relates to the upstream firmware tree. An agent implementing v0.1 cloned meshtastic/firmware on a separate machine, edited it in place, and reported success in beads — work evaporated when the clone was discarded. Eight beads (cdo,7si,fkf,q18,plu,61d,fvu,jul) closed claiming work that produced no output in this repo. v0.2 fixes this with: (1) firmware-overlay/ for new files, (2) patches/apply.py anchor-substitution patcher for modified files, (3) meshtastic-firmware-pin one-line SHA, (4) multi-stage Dockerfile baking the pinned upstream into a layer, (5) GitHub Actions release+PR+drift workflows. Build infrastructure (BEAD-1 through BEAD-4) ships before any C++. Prior art: github.com/soniccyclone/Meshtastic-Firmware-Friend-Finder-Edition."}
